



Esteemed friend
London 1 Decemr 1774



We wrote thee 14 Novemr  the Nancy Capt. Wise as  copy annexd to which beg leave to refer theesince then illegible have received none of thy favors.1
We send thee inclosed the Kings Speech by which thou wilt see the resolution of Government relative to the Colonies we much wish some expedient may be adopted amicably to settle all disputes.2 We are with great regard thy assured friends

Hanburys & Lloyd

